    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A sodium compound which in its anhydrous form occurs in nature as a chemical precipitate found in the minerals thenardite and mirabilite. It may also be obtained synthetically by mixing sodium chloride and sulfuric acid. As a solid or powder, sodium sulphate is used in the manufacture of various products. In conservation science it is addressed as an agent of salt damage to stone.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
